Model Training and Evaluation¶

Dummy classifier as our baseline model.

In [ ]:
import numpy as np
from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report

dummy_clf = DummyClassifier(strategy="most_frequent")
dummy_clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

y_pred_dummy = dummy_clf.predict(X_test)

dummy_clf.score(X_test, y_test)

CNN model

In [ ]:
from keras import optimizers
from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers.convolutional import Conv1D, MaxPooling1D
from keras.layers import Dense, LSTM, RepeatVector, TimeDistributed, Flatten
In [ ]:
model_cnn = Sequential()
model_cnn.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=(2), activation='relu', input_shape=(76,1)))
model_cnn.add(MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2))
model_cnn.add(Flatten())
model_cnn.add(Dense(50, activation='relu'))
model_cnn.add(Dense(1))
model_cnn.compile(loss='mse', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model_cnn.summary()

Model Perfomance Comparison¶

Now we will compare the perfomance of Dummy Classifier, CNN and SVM using the accuracy, precision, Recall and f1-score evaluation metrics.

In [ ]:
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
from sklearn.metrics import recall_score
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score
from sklearn.metrics import precision_score

dummy_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_dummy)
dummy_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_dummy, average='binary')
dummy_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_dummy, average='binary')
dummy_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_dummy, average='binary')

cnn_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_cnn)
cnn_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_cnn, average='binary')
cnn_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_cnn, average='binary')
cnn_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_cnn, average='binary')

svm_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_svc)
svm_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_svc, average='binary')
svm_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_svc, average='binary')
svm_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_svc, average='binary')

Ploting the different evaluation score

In [ ]:
barWidth = 0.25
fig = plt.subplots(figsize =(12, 8))
 
dummy_score = [dummy_accuracy,dummy_precision,dummy_f1,dummy_recall]
cnn_score = [cnn_accuracy,cnn_precision,cnn_f1,cnn_recall]
svm_score = [svm_accuracy,svm_precision,svm_f1,svm_recall]

br1 = np.arange(len(dummy_score))
br2 = [x + barWidth for x in br1]
br3 = [x + barWidth for x in br2]
 
plt.bar(br1, dummy_score, color ='darkorange', width = barWidth,
        edgecolor ='grey', label ='Dummy Classifier')
plt.bar(br2, cnn_score, color ='mediumblue', width = barWidth,
        edgecolor ='grey', label ='CNN')
plt.bar(br3, svm_score, color ='k', width = barWidth,
        edgecolor ='grey', label ='SVM')
 
plt.xlabel('Evaluation Criteria', fontweight ='bold', fontsize = 15)
plt.ylabel('Score', fontweight ='bold', fontsize = 15)
plt.xticks([r + barWidth for r in range(len(dummy_score))],
        ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'F1-Score', 'Recall'])
 
plt.legend()
plt.show()
